    "description": "We at Pfizer India Digital Technologies are looking for an experienced Medical Officer based out of Ahmedabad. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Pfizer India Digital Technologies:\nPfizer India Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Pfizer India Digital Technologies!",
